tsprov is a derivative work of `prov`, the Python implementation of the W3C PROV
Data Model (https://github.com/trungdong/prov). Its in-memory model, serializers,
and value-equality semantics are ported from that library, and its PROV-JSON test
corpus is the oracle tsprov is validated against. `prov` is used under the MIT
License, reproduced in full below.

